I think the logic of this method could be simplified to:

``` csharp
using (var it = projects.GetEnumerator())
{
    if (!it.MoveNext())
    {
        return Enumerable.Empty<Document>()
    }

    var first = it.Current;
    var filePaths = new HashSet<string>(StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
    while (it.MoveNext())
    {
        foreach (var doc in it.Documents)
        {
            filePaths.Add(doc.FilePath);
        }
    }

    return first.Documents.Where(d => filePaths.Contains(d.FilePath));
}
```

This would avoid all of the internal allocations in `Intersect`

